This is a prerelease of Herwig++ for e+e- collisions.  This version is
only distributed for tutorial purposes during the workshop
Monte Carlo Tools for the LHC (CERN, July 2003). 

DO NOT USE IT FOR SERIOUS PHYSICS STUDIES! 

What you need:
==============
- Linux operating system;
- GNU C/C++ compiler  gcc > 3.2, see
  http://www.gnu.org/directory/gcc.html
- CLHEP version 1.8.0.0  or higher. See
  http://wwwasd.web.cern.ch/wwwasd/lhc++/clhep/DISTRIBUTION/clhep.html
- ThePEG v1.0 (alpha release) 
  http://www.thep.lu.se/ThePEG/>ThePEG

See INSTALL for installation instructions. 

Philip Stephens, Stefan Gieseke (21 July 2003)

